  "prompt": "How many credits must you take for 2nd semester in VIT?",
  "response": "The number of credits you need to take during the second semester at Vellore Institute of Technology (VIT) can vary based on your specific program and the curriculum structure for that academic year. However, typically, undergraduate students are required to enroll in a certain number of credits each semester to stay on track for graduation. This often ranges between 18 to 25 credits per semester. \n\nFor exact information regarding your second-semester credit requirements, you should consult your program guide or academic advisor at VIT, as they can provide details tailored to your specific course of study and batch. Additionally, the information might be available on the university\u2019s official student portal or academic handbook.",
